Introduction

Alyssa is a Malaysian-born trainee and former contestant on SBS survival show Universe Ticket. She was 18 years old when she participated in the survival show, which aimed to form a new girl group under F&F Entertainment. She is a multilingual who is fluent in Malay and English and conversational in Korean and Thai.

Alyssa is known for her graceful yet powerful stage presence, earning her the nickname "Charisma Monster" among fans. During her time on Universe Ticket, she showcased her dance skills, including a performance of BLACKPINK's "DDU-DU DDU-DU," and was ranked 12th in the pro-voting standings before voluntarily exiting the show in Episode 4 due to personal reasons.
